turns.speaker: DOCTOR

turns.text: That, that is correct, yes. I'm experiencing discomfort in my chest.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>

turns.text: Sure, um, it's been ongoing for, a couple of hours now.

turns.text: And it's more, it feels like it's pressure, <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/> discomfort, than more, than a pain.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um, if I, had to <UNIN/>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: If <UNSURE>I</UNSURE>, if I had to describe what <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/> <UNSURE>discomfort</UNSURE> feeling, it's, it's like someone's sitting on my chest. <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: <UNSURE>And</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yeah.

turns.text: Uh, yes I do <UNSURE>smoke, yeah</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK, <UNIN/>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Ten being, very sort of, unbearable and severe pain. Seven is.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Quite manageable, <UNSURE>well</UNSURE>, it's quite <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>, and how about now?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um, it's still the same.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK, and tell me before this happened, what were you doing?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yeah.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um, I was, <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/> <UNSURE>relaxing</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK, and are you normally fit and well? So, are you <UNIN/> normally OK to garden as you would?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Uh, yes.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: Great, and apart from this, do you have any other medical problems?

turns.text: Um, high cholesterol, and, I've had hypertension, <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/> <UNSURE>hypertension</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: No, I don't take any medicine.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK, and are you allergic to anything?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Uh, <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK. So, let me summarise what you've told me already. You were gardening a few hours ago, and you experienced chest discomfort, which was roughly seven out of ten.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNSURE>And it</UNSURE> feels more like someone's sitting on your chest, as opposed to pain.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yeah.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yes, that's <UNSURE>great</UNSURE>.

turns.text: And apart from this, have you noticed anything else unusual, specifically with your breathing?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Uh, yes I have. Um, I've got shortness of breath. And I feel slightly, light-headed.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK, and is that getting worse or better?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um, it's remained the same. Although, I would say recently I've noticed, in terms of sort of breathing, I've had, <UNSURE>some</UNSURE> difficulty <UNSURE>climbing</UNSURE> the stairs. And, if I have to sort of walk uphill, there's that sort of challenge as well.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: And when you get short of breath, when you're walking up the stairs, have you noticed any pain?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um, no pain as such, but there's often calf pain and, leg <UNSURE>swellings</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: OK. So, let me confirm. You have the pressure at the moment, and you have shortness of breath, is that correct?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: That is correct, yes.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNIN/>. So, given what you've told me about your past medical history. I think it might be worth, you calling an ambulance.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: OK.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNIN/> get you to the hospital as soon as possible. Because, my concern is, it might be something to do with your heart.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: So, <UNSURE>While</UNSURE> <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/> to you, I will ring an ambulance. Who, should come to your address.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Ohh, OK.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: <UNSURE>Ohh</UNSURE> right.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: But in the meantime, I think we should stay on the phone. So I can gather some more information, that we can give to the paramedics. Is that OK?

turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>.

turns.text: Um, should I, be concerned about anything?

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: It's nothing to worry about at the moment, but, given that you've got high blood pressure and high cholesterol, and you've got some chest pain. I'm always worried about the heart first, before anything else.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: <UNIN/>, OK, <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNIN/>, <UNSURE>and we</UNSURE>, and we need to look after your heart before anything else.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: So, apart from this <UNIN/> light-headedness, and this chest discomfort, have you <UNIN/> noticed anything else unusual?

turns.text: Um, nothing, else unusual. Um, I'm not sure if I spoke to you about nausea?

turns.text: I've noticed nausea, but no vomiting, yet.

turns.text: <UNSURE>Did</UNSURE> you have anything to eat or drink this morning?

turns.text: Um, no.

turns.text: And you feel, still feel nauseous at the moment?

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: I have, yeah. I am, yeah.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: So, I have a couple of other questions to ask you, and I'm gonna reel them off. So, <UNSURE>apologies</UNSURE> for not letting you talk very much.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: No, that's fine.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Uh, yes. There is some pain in my left shoulder and <UNSURE>arm</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Uh, no.

turns.text: Uh, no.

turns.text: Good.

turns.text: And have you noticed any problems going to the loo?

turns.text: Uh, no problems going to the loo.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Um.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yes, however, there's some problems just, performing daily activities. Um, like I said, with the difficulties climbing up the stairs and going uphill. Um, I try to limit my daily activity to just moving around the house, nothing too strenuous.

turns.text: <INAUDIBLE_SPEECH/>

turns.text: And, do you live at home with your wife at the moment?

turns.text: Uh, yes.

turns.speaker: DOCTOR
turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>. I would suggest, if she's there, you let her know that, you'll both be having an adventure to the hospital today. So, she might need to get your things together.

turns.text: <UNSURE>OK</UNSURE>.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Got it, OK.

turns.text: Don't <UNSURE>take</UNSURE> any of those medications.

turns.text: OK.

turns.speaker: PATIENT

turns.text: So, when they do come, there are two things they will be worried about.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: OK.

turns.text: The one is your chest, so, your heart. And <UNSURE>the second</UNSURE> is your breathing, which is your lungs.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: Yes.

turns.speaker: PATIENT
turns.text: OK.

turns.text: OK.

turns.text: Ohh, that's great.
